                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/relg-454" class="program-course-title">
              RELG 454 Modern Hindu Thought (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-35081" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Religious Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Religious Studies              : A study of the developments in religious thought with special reference to such thinkers as Ram Mohan Roy, Dayananda Saraswati, Ramakrishna, Vivekananda, Gandhi, Tilak, Aurobindo, and Radhakrishnan.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Shital Sharma (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: RELG 252 </li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
